def print_bold(text):
    text_bold = '\x1b[1;30;47m'+text+ '\x1b[0m'
    print(text_bold)
def glance(x,n=5):
    try:
        iterator = iter(x)
    except:
        print(x)
        return
    else:
        if type(x) == str or len(str(x)) <= 50:
            print(x)
            return
        if type(x) == dict:
            iterator = x.items()
        i = 0
        for ele in iterator:
            if i >= n:
                break
            glance(ele,n)
            i += 1

# post lengths
def plot_series(series,ax):
    series.plot(kind='density', ax=ax, title='Density Plot of %s' % series.name)
    # Access the child artists and calculate the mean of the resulting array
    mean_val = np.mean(series)
    max_val = np.max(series)
    max_y = np.max(ax.get_children()[0]._y)
    # Annotate points
    ax.annotate('mean', xy=(mean_val, 0.7*max_y), xytext=(mean_val+0.1*max_val, 0.6*max_y),
                arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', width=1, headwidth=4),
                )
    # vertical dotted line originating at mean value
    ax.axvline(mean_val, linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    median_val = np.median(series)
    # Annotate points
    ax.annotate('median', xy=(median_val, 0.3*max_y), xytext=(median_val+0.1*max_val, 0.4*max_y),
                arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', width=1, headwidth=4),
                )
    # vertical dotted line originating at mean value
    ax.axvline(median_val, linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)

    # Annotate points
    ax.annotate('max', xy=(max_val, 0.3*max_y), xytext=(max_val+0.1*max_val, 0.4*max_y),
                arrowprops=dict(facecolor='black', width=1, headwidth=4),
                )
    # vertical dotted line originating at mean value
    ax.axvline(max_val, linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2)
    
plot_columns = ['count','reaction','share','comment']
fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(plot_columns),figsize=(16,6*len(plot_columns)))
ax_count = 0
for col in plot_columns:
    plot_series(df[col], axes[ax_count])
    ax_count+=1

In [9]:
# Compare Month Pattern of each year
df_analyse = df.copy()
df_analyse['year'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(df_analyse['date']).year
df_analyse['month'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(df_analyse['date']).month
counts = {}
for index,row in df_analyse.iterrows():
    year = row['year']
    month = row['month']
    if year not in counts:
        counts[year] = {}
    if month not in counts[year]:
        counts[year][month] = 0
    counts[year][month] += 1
df_counts = pd.DataFrame(counts).sort_index()
df_counts.plot(figsize = (16,10))

top_5_pages = df_analyse[df_analyse['page_name'] != '-']['page_name'].value_counts().head(5).index.tolist()
df_top_5_year = pd.DataFrame()
df_top_5_month = pd.DataFrame()
for page in top_5_pages:
    temp_df = df_analyse[df_analyse['page_name'] == page]
    temp_series = temp_df['title']
    temp_series.index = temp_df['date']
    df_top_5_year[page] = temp_series.resample('Y').count()
    df_top_5_month[page] = temp_series.resample('M').count()
df_top_5_year.plot(figsize=(16,5), title='Top 5 Pages Yearly Count')
df_top_5_month.plot(figsize=(16,5), title='Top 5 Pages Monthly Count')

    plot_series = df_analyse[df_analyse['Platform'] == platform]['lang'].value_counts()
    ax = plot_series.plot.pie(figsize=(16,10),title='Post Languages',labels=[' ']*len(plot_series),autopct='%1.1f%%' )
    ax.legend(labels=plot_series.index)
    plt.title('Language Proportion for Platform: %s' % platform)
    plt.show()

entities_dict = {}
def annotate_entities(text):
    try:
        entities = entity_model.predict(text)
    except Exception as e:
        return 'Error'
    for (token, entity) in entities:
        if entity not in entities_dict:
            entities_dict[entity] = 0
        entities_dict[entity] += 1
    return entities

pos_dict = {}
error = 0
def annotate_pos(text):
    try:
        pos = pos_model.predict(text)
        for (word, tag) in pos:
            if tag not in pos_dict:
                pos_dict[tag] = 0
            pos_dict[tag] += 1
        return pos
    except:
        try:
            tokens = text.split(' ')
            pos = [pos_model.predict(x)[0] for x in tokens]
            return pos
        except:
            global error
            error += 1
            return 'Error'
df_analyse['pos'] = df_analyse['title'].progress_apply(annotate_pos)
print('errors: %s' % error)
df_analyse.sample(5)

In [ ]:



    


 



    













In [40]:



    


def stem(tokens,lang_group):
    if lang_group == 'malay':
        try:
            return stem_model.stem(' '.join(tokens)).split(' ')
        except:
            return tokens
    elif lang_group == 'eng':
        try:
            return [lemmatizer.lemmatize(t) for t in tokens]
        except:
            return tokens
    else:
        print('unidentified lang_group: %s' % lang_group)
df_analyse['stem'] = df_analyse.progress_apply(lambda x: stem(x['tokens'],x['lang_group']), axis = 1)
